\":\"heading\"}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"2019330c\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"margin\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":0,\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":0,\"isLinked\":false},\"padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"100\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"layout\":\"full_width\",\"padding_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"050\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"549b146f\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"22ad4426\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"title\":\"A place to breathe.\",\"align\":\"center\",\"title_color\":\"#424242\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_size\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":26},\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\",\"typography_font_weight\":\"400\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"heading\"},{\"id\":\"5c483c3c\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"gap\":\"wide\",\"structure\":\"20\",\"margin\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"50\",\"right\":0,\"bottom\":\"0\",\"left\":0,\"isLinked\":false},\"layout\":\"full_width\",\"margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"1\",\"right\":0,\"bottom\":\"1\",\"left\":0,\"isLinked\":true}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"7542bf6b\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"623679d6\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>The power of words is that a life can be launched with as little as a single phrase, an uplifting word or an act of kindness. Think of the power we wield and the impact we can make if we become more intentional about encouraging our children. Our words are often the very things that help create future dreams. And sometimes those dreams are to be just like us<\\/p><p>It\\u2019s not just about whether you were born into an under-resourced environment, but it\'s how you interact with your child in that environment that seems to make a difference<\\/p><p>Though a word gap can have lasting consequences, the good news is that all parents talk to their children at least some of the time. If parents understand that quality interactions are more important than quantity, then all children could benefit.<\\/p>\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":true},{\"id\":\"df2fb7a\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":50,\"_inline_size\":null},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"410df1df\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"editor\":\"<p>The more social experiences they have, whether with their parents or with any other caregivers around them, the more they will learn, she adds<\\/p><p>As these children were all from lower-income backgrounds, the results show that poverty alone is not what predisposes a child to poorer language skills.<\\/p><p>What is key here is that the influence of poverty on how parents communicated with their children is explained by how much the parents knew about child development<\\/p>\",\"typography_typography\":\"custom\",\"typography_font_family\":\"Open Sans\"},\"elements\":[],\"widgetType\":\"text-editor\"}],\"isInner\":true}],\"isInner\":true}],\"isInner\":false}],\"isInner\":false},{\"id\":\"5824cde\",\"elType\":\"section\",\"settings\":{\"padding\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"0\",\"right\":\"0\",\"bottom\":\"40\",\"left\":\"0\",\"isLinked\":false},\"margin_mobile\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"top\":\"\",\"right\":0,\"bottom\":\"\",\"left\":0,\"isLinked\":true}},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"30139aa3\",\"elType\":\"column\",\"settings\":{\"_column_size\":100},\"elements\":[{\"id\":\"4d9518b1\",\"elType\":\"widget\",\"settings\":{\"text\":\"TALK TO US, WE CARE\",\"align\":\"center\",\"icon_align\":\"right\",\"icon_indent\":{\"unit\":\"px\",\"size\":14},\"button_text_color\":\"#595959\",\"background_color\":\"#ffffff\",\"hover_color\":\"#262626\",\"button_hover_border_color\":\"#26